@startuml
title REQ-002 Workspace Shell And Role Pages - Architecture
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor User

package "Entry Layer" {
  [main.py] as MainEntry
  [ProgramSelectorWindow] as Selector
}

package "Project Context" {
  [project_loader] as Loader
  [ProjectDefinition] as ProjectDefinition
}

package "Workspace Shell" {
  [ProjectWorkspaceWindow] as Workspace
  [WorkspaceNavigationWidget] as Navigation
  [LiveSessionPanel] as Session
  [ConsolePanel] as Console
  [WorkspacePageStack] as PageStack
}

package "Role Pages" {
  [OverviewPage] as OverviewPage
  [FirmwarePage] as FirmwarePage
  [MechanicalPage] as MechanicalPage
  [ApplicationProductionPage] as ApplicationPage
  [SettingsPage] as SettingsPage
}

package "Transition Layer" {
  [WorkspaceRuntimeBridge] as Bridge
  [Existing dialogs and runtime hooks] as LegacyHooks
}

User --> Selector : choose project
MainEntry --> Selector : create + show
Selector --> Loader : load_available_projects()
Loader --> ProjectDefinition : build typed project
Selector --> Workspace : open(project_definition)

Workspace --> Navigation
Workspace --> Session
Workspace --> Console
Workspace --> PageStack

PageStack --> OverviewPage
PageStack --> FirmwarePage
PageStack --> MechanicalPage
PageStack --> ApplicationPage
PageStack --> SettingsPage

Workspace --> Bridge : request transitional data/actions
Bridge --> LegacyHooks : use narrow adapters

note right of Workspace
Phase 2 changes the top-level runtime shape:
- selector opens the workspace shell
- shell owns routing and layout
- legacy logic is bridged, not promoted
end note
@enduml
